Question:
Which of the following knots in the figure consist of more than one loop of rope?

Options:
A: \(P, R\) and \(T\)
B: \(R, S\) and \(T\)
C: \(P, R, S\) and \(T\)
D: all of \(P, Q, R, S\) and \(T\)
E: none of \(\mathrm{A}, \mathrm{B}, \mathrm{C}\) or \(\mathrm{D}\)

message.content:
We want the knots that consist of more than one loop of rope (i.e., more than one separate closed component).

- In \(P\) and \(Q\), each diagram shows a single closed loop twisted around itself.
- In \(R\), there are two separate closed loops (a two-component link).
- In \(S\), there are three separate closed loops.
- In \(T\), there are also two separate closed loops.

Thus the knots with more than one loop are \(R, S,\) and \(T\).

Answer:B
